<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Yearly to Hourly Calculator</h1>
    <p style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:2rem">Find out how much $75,000 a year is per hour. Adjust the hours and days to match your work schedule.</p>

    <label for="salary">Yearly Salary ($)</label>
    <input type="number" id="salary" value="75000" />

    <label for="hours">Hours Worked per Week</label>
    <input type="number" id="hours" value="40" />

    <label for="weeks">Working Weeks per Year</label>
    <input type="number" id="weeks" value="52" />

    <button onclick="calculateHourly()">Calculate Hourly Rate</button>

    <div class="result" id="result"></div>

    <div class="faq">
      <h2>üìò FAQ: Yearly to Hourly Conversion</h2>

      <p><strong>How do you calculate $65,000 per year into hourly?</strong><br>
      Divide your annual salary by the number of hours you work in a year (e.g., 65,000 / (40√ó52)). Our calculator does the math instantly.</p>

      <p><strong>What if I work less than 40 hours?</strong><br>
      You can enter any number of hours you actually work per week. This adjusts your hourly rate accordingly.</p>

      <p><strong>Is this before or after taxes?</strong><br>
      This is a gross pay calculator. It doesn‚Äôt account for taxes or deductions ‚Äî it shows what you make per hour on paper.</p>

      <p><strong>Why is this helpful?</strong><br>
      Converting yearly income to hourly wage helps with budgeting, job comparisons, and freelance rate planning.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="back-link">
      <a href="/">‚Üê Back to All Calculators</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <script is:client="load">
    function calculateHourly() {
      const salary = parseFloat(document.getElementById("salary").value);
      const hours = parseFloat(document.getElementById("hours").value);
      const weeks = parseFloat(document.getElementById("weeks").value);
      const resultEl = document.getElementById("result");

      if (isNaN(salary) || isNaN(hours) || isNaN(weeks) || hours <= 0 || weeks <= 0) {
        resultEl.textContent = "Please enter valid numbers.";
        return;
      }

      const totalHours = hours * weeks;
      const hourly = salary / totalHours;
      resultEl.textContent = `$${salary.toLocaleString()} per year is approximately $${hourly.toFixed(2)} per hour.`;
    }
  </script>
</body>
